The paper deals with the estimation of time delay and Doppler stretch using the ambiguity function, which is a common technique in signal processing and communication systems. This suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) are likely categories. The paper also discusses the performance of the random stepped-frequency (RSF) signal, which is a type of synthetic wideband signal, indicating that cs.SP (Signal Processing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper presents theoretical results on mean square errors and Cramer-Rao lower bounds, which are common topics in statistical learning and optimization, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as well.
